Syaikhul Islam mengatakan,

واللهُ تَعَالَى قَدْ جَعَلَ أَكْمَلَ المُؤْمِنِيْنَ إِيْمَانًا أَعْظَمُهُمْ بَلاَءً “Allah akan memberikan cobaan terberat bagi setiap orang mukmin yang sempurna imannya.”[3]
.
Semakin kuat iman, semakin berat cobaan, namun semakin Allah cinta. Rasulullah shallallahu ‘alaihi wa sallam bersabda,

إِنَّ عِظَمَ الْجَزَاءِ مَعَ عِظَمِ الْبَلاَءِ وَإِنَّ اللَّهَ إِذَا أَحَبَّ قَوْمًا ابْتَلاَهُمْ فَمَنْ رَضِىَ فَلَهُ الرِّضَا وَمَنْ سَخِطَ فَلَهُ السَّخَطُ “Sesungguhnya balasan terbesar dari ujian yang berat. Jika Allah mencintai suatu kaum, maka Allah akan memberikan cobaan kepada mereka. Barangsiapa ridho, maka Allah pun ridho. Dan barangsiapa murka (tidak suka pada cobaan tersebut, pen), maka baginya murka Allah.”[6]

Nations make war to protect their interests and national gain. If not, the people would starve. But the battleground was always our small village, our small land. And each time, our land laid waste and people left impoverished. After many wars, the great land stabilized. And our small country was left to bear the wound of wars. We both want the same thing. We both want the peace our master spoke of. You and I are no different. We’re both working for our own justice.

The justice I have meted out against larger nations, is exactly the same as what you’re trying to mete out against me. Everyone feels the pain of loss the same. We both know that pain. You are working for your justice, and I for mine. We are just ordinary people driven to revenge in the name of justice. But if revenge is called justice, then that justice breeds yet more revenge. And becomes a chain of hatred. Living within it, aware of the past, predicting the future. That is what it means to know history. We cannot help but know that people cannot understand each other. -Mushashi Kishimoto

FOOT DRILLS FOR SUPINATORS

We are going to go over some specific drills for all my 🍲 supinators out there. Supination is motion of rolling to the outside of the foot with walking and or running movements. This leads to weakness in the peroneals (outer portion of the calves) and an inability to roll through the heel to midfoot then onto the big toe.
.
Not all supination is bad you actually do use a portion of it in the walking/gait cycle. However, when it becomes the only way you walk with every step, that can be problematic. So tonight we are going to work on rolling our weight from the heel 🔛 midfoot 🔛 on through the big toe incoporating some Vele's lean.
.
Here are some things to keep in mind as you go through these movements:
.
👣Wall Lean - let your weight shift from your heels into big toes. Go up on them and allow yourself to kinda fall into the wall.
.
👣Vele's Lean - heels stay planted here. Simple lean forward but try to control yourself from falling forward into the wall by driving your big toe into the ground. For fun, try stopping with the outer toes and see how well it goes. It'll highlight the importance if that big toe very quickly.
.
👣One Leg Wall Lean - go onto one foot and roll your weight from heel to toe by falling into the wall.
.
👣One Leg Vele's Lean - again, heels stay planted. Lean forward and control yourself through that big toe! This one is TOUGH 😣 but you can do it.
.
Do 3 sets 6-8 reps. Be sure to control the movement. If you want exercises to strengthen the grip in your toes take a peek👀 at the previous post.
.
🎵Black Coast-"Feel Something"
.
Got a 🙋‍♂️ friend who supinates? Tag them and show them some 😙 love.
.

Hip Strategy
----------
Want to lessen your risk for injury when performing sport-related tasks such as landing or cutting?
. 
Learning to implement a 'hip strategy' when decelerating is thought to be an effective technique for taking advantage of the force generating capability of the large hip extensors (glutes) and knee extensors (quads) and decreasing overall stress to passive subsystem structures such as ligaments, cartilage and bone.
.
The hip strategy consists of three elements, which are depicted nicely in this video.
1️⃣ Flex the trunk
2️⃣ Flex the hips
3️⃣Avoid excessive anterior knee migration .
All of these strategies will help encourage force attenuation by the neuromuscular system and reduce injury risk and/or the development of pain.
.
.
.

Hello la #teamhalfbody 🔥 ! 
Lundi j'ai croisé @amaury.thimonier qui ne me connaissais pas. Il est venu me demander pourquoi je me filmai, si cela était personnel ou si je le diffusais. 
Après avoir regardé mon compte instagram, il est revenu me voir pour me dire à quel point ce que je faisais était bien, qu'il aimait par dessus tout ce genre de personne qui donne le meilleur d'elle même quoi qu'il arrive. Que j'étais quelqu'un d'exceptionnel et dont il fallait qu'on parle.

J'aimerai juste revenir sur le terme "exceptionnel". Je ne suis pas un super héros doté de super pouvoir les ami(e)s 😊. Je ne suis qu'un homme qui certe en a pris plein la gueule, mais qui n'est toujours qu'un simple humain. 
Tout ça pour vous dire les ami(e)s que vous en êtes TOUS capable ! Ce que je fais n'est en aucun cas surhumain. Il vous suffit simplement de trouver LA motivation qui vous fera mettre un pied devant l'autre chaque jour. Ça peut être un amour, ça peut être un rêve,  ça peut être simplement le fais de vouloir vivre. 
Dans la vie, il n'y a pas de destin. Il n'y a que les choix que nous faisons. Alors faite le bon choix et battez vous 💪 !
